## Completion Criteria

- [ ] All Goals and Requirements (R1–R4) met
- [ ] Build and test suite green
- [ ] Manual checks: chains in order, order stable across edits, language switch does not reorder
- [ ] PR opened per the repo's fork workflow

## Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|------------|
| Users expect the exact in-game (reverse unlock-time) order and notice the difference | Low/Medium | Documented decision; the progression order is stable and arguably more useful for planning |
| Prerequisite data gaps make a chain look flat | Low | Deterministic tiebreak keeps it sensible; data maintained via the DB pipeline |
| A quest cannot be ranked (missing identifier) | Low | Deterministic fallback places it last; order stays stable |

